100.title: Ultimate Edition
100.plot: Episode's alternate title: '100. EPIZODA PRIME TIMEA: Ova gospoda godinama ismijavaju Hrvate, evo sto Hrvati misle o njima.' Part clip-show and part spoof of behind-the-scenes look at the people who make the show.

101.title: Sto i jedan referendum
101.plot: Episode's alternate title: 'Imaju li Hrvati uopce mentalni kapacitet za glasovanje na referendumu?'

102.title: Premijersko karanje
102.plot: Episode's alternate title: 'Jugokomunisti mrze ovu epizodu Prime Timea jer smo konacno, za promjenu, domoljubni.' Borna tries to be 'patriotic' for once and see this week's scandals from a 'positive' angle.

103.title: Da bog da sve izgubili
103.plot: Episode's alternate title: 'Draga hrvatska reprezentacijo, dabogda sve izgubili.'

104.title: S konja na Marasa
104.plot: As FIFA World Cup begins, Borna explores whether the country (along with most of the world) is rapidly slipping towards some Futurist form of fascist society and if there's anyone who can stop this trend (spoiler alert: probably not).

105.title: Plenki, kralj Afrike
105.plot: Alternate title: "Dok ste gledali utakmicu, netko vas je opet pokusao opljackati." Domagoj tries to get the country to stop obsessing over the FIFA World Cup for a second and realize how disastrous the pension reform will be for them.

106.title: Tekma zivota
106.plot: Alternate title: "Hrvatska ima povijesni rezultat, ali jalni i zlobni jezici stalno nesto dobacuju s kauca." As FIFA World Cup nears its end, Borna analyzes "how the Croatian team did so well" (the government's shady Agrokor deal).

107.title: Kraj broncanog doba
107.plot: Alternate title: "Borna Sor izravno s terena provjerava je li Hrvatska stvarno izasla iz broncanog doba."

108.title: Zajednistvo
108.plot: Alternate title: "Neka pati koga smeta - Hrvatska je vice prvak svijeta."

109.title: Ljetina
109.plot: Alternate title: "Repriza svih repriza." With Domagoj still on summer vacation, Borna takes a break as well, and hosts from his magic couch this clip show retrospective of top moments that the summer of 2018 had to offer.

110.title: Top lista scenarista
110.plot: Alternate title: "Repriza svih repriza 2." In this clip show, Domagoj's clones in DC Comics t-shirts watch his best moments on Prime Time to come up with a script for the new episode.

111.title: Dan zahvalnosti
111.plot: Alternate title: "Teorija o dva razlicita Thompsona." Domagoj returns from his summer vacation, cleans himself up and returns to form by taking on one of the most sacred Croatian cows - the ultra-nationalist singer Thompson.

112.title: Zbilja Velika Gospa
112.plot: Alternate title: "Nahranimo nadbiskupa Hranica." After receiving actual death threats over his comments about Thompson, Domagoj puts on a combat helmet and analyzes the latest scandals of The Catholic Church in Croatia and abroad.

113.title: Orbanizacija
113.plot: Alternate title: "Orbanizacija Hrvatske." After sending his unsuspecting body double Ivan to be assassinated instead of him, Domagoj shows how good the ruling party is at avoiding any and all responsibility for their criminal (in)actions.

114.title: Prime Timeline
114.plot: Alternate title: "Veliki gradjanski rad u Novom Zagrebu."

115.title: Spomenik domovini
115.plot: Alternate title: "Pogani jezik iz Pogane Vlake."

116.title: Jogurtin rat
116.plot: Alternate title: "Jogurt samo neparnim danima." Borna enjoys some yogurt while analyzing President Kitarovic's claim that life in Croatia is so much better now than in communist Yugoslavia because now people can have all kinds of yogurt.

117.title: Sam svoj SUBNOR-ovac
117.plot: Alternate title: "Predsjednica ima intoleranciju na laktozu, cinjenice i izbjeglice."

118.title: Unutarnji prijatelj
118.plot: Alternate title: "James Bond drzava - Hrvatska, Republika Hrvatska."

119.title: Prica o Vasi Kurvanjskom
119.plot: Alternate title: "Znate l' pricu o Vasi Kurvanjskom?"

121.title: Kiretaza na livadi

imdb.plot outline: Not unlike Jon Stewart on Daily Show, political satirists Borna Sor and Domagoj Zovak analyze the latest big scandals in Croatian politics and society each week, using their razor-sharp wit, bitter humor, biting satire, creative pop culture references, darkly comedic sketches and hilarious montages to create a painfully poignant, brutally honest and truly heartfelt critique of widespread political and moral corruption in country and, occasionally, around the world, that's meant to entertain, offer catharsis and most importantly appeal to reason and hopefully change the society for the better, one viewer at the time.
imdb.title: Prime Time
plot: Each week, Borna Sor and Domagoj Zovak analyze the latest scandals in Croatia, using their razor-sharp wit, biting satire and brutally honest, painfully poignant and truly heartfelt critique of widespread political and moral corruption.

Not unlike Jon Stewart on Daily Show, political satirists Borna Sor and Domagoj Zovak analyze the latest big scandals in Croatian politics and society each week, using their razor-sharp wit, bitter humor, biting satire, creative pop culture references, darkly comedic sketches and hilarious montages to create a painfully poignant, brutally honest and truly heartfelt critique of widespread political and moral corruption in country and, occasionally, around the world, that's meant to entertain, offer catharsis and most importantly appeal to reason and hopefully change the society for the better, one viewer at the time.
